> Looks like the JMX file is incomplete or mangled.

Any reason for that file is corrupted?
Jmx not changed this in recent days. (I was working until 10/08)
This already happened twice with this version 2.7

The error in the file says:

no more data available - expected end tags </elementProp></collectionProp></elementProp></HTTPSamplerProxy></hashTree></hashTree></hashTree></hashTree></hashTree></hashTree></jmeterTestPlan> to close start tag <elementProp> etc,

which is a clear description of the problem.

It's not possible to say what has caused the JMX file to be truncated; it could be any number of issues, including lack of disk space, system crash, hardware fault etc.
